&lt;h3&gt;Diversity, Equity &amp;amp; Inclusion&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a fully-remote international company, diversity is baked into our DNA. Here’s how our CEO, Sid Yadav, frames our hiring mission: “let’s find talent in underserved and under-represented corners of the world, set them up to do the best work of their lives, and in turn, change their life.” To achieve this hiring mission, we offer competitive&amp;nbsp;U.S. benchmarked&amp;nbsp;compensation no matter where someone’s located in the world, and we proactively seek candidates who expand representation of backgrounds, cultures and lived experiences in our teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Equal Employment Opportunity&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Circle is an equal opportunity employer and as such, we do not discriminate on the basis of race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, age, disability, or any other characteristic protected by applicable laws.&amp;nbsp;If you require any accommodations during the recruitment process, please let us know and we will work with you to meet your needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;&quot;&gt;
&lt;h3 class=&quot;&quot;&gt;How We Use Candidate Data&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Circle, we are committed to protecting your personal information. As a job applicant, the personal data you provide to us is collected and processed in accordance with the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR)&lt;/strong&gt; in the EU and the &lt;strong&gt;California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA)&lt;/strong&gt;. This notice outlines the types of personal information we collect, the purpose for collecting it, and your rights.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Information We Collect:&lt;/strong&gt; We collect the following categories of personal information from job applicants:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contact information (such as name, email address, phone number)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Employment history and qualifications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Education history&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;References and any other information you choose to share with us during the application process&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Purpose of Collection:&lt;/strong&gt; We collect this information for the following purposes:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To assess your qualifications and suitability for the position&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To communicate with you during the recruitment process&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To comply with legal and regulatory obligations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Rights Under GDPR and CCPA:&lt;/strong&gt; You have the following rights regarding your personal information:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The right to request access to the personal information we hold about you.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The right to request the deletion of your personal information, subject to certain legal exceptions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The right to opt out of the sale of your personal information (Note: We do not sell personal information).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information about how we handle your personal data or to exercise your rights, please refer to our full &lt;a href=&quot;https://circle.so/privacy&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Privacy Policy&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;By submitting your application, you acknowledge that you have read and understood this privacy notice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;h2&gt;About Us&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Circle is building the world’s leading all-in-one platform for online communities. We make it possible for creators, coaches, educators, and businesses to bring together their audience with engaging discussions, live streams, events, chat, courses, and payments — all in one place, all under their own brand.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re proud to be a fully remote company of around 170 (and growing!) team members from 30+ countries around the world. We seek exceptional individuals around the world, set them up to do the best work of their lives, and in turn, create a meaningful impact in their own lives. We don&#39;t track hours, but we do manage for high expectations very closely. We collaborate across time zones, are highly async, and like to document a lot.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Twice a year, we bring the whole company together in beautiful places around the world for our company offsites. So far, we’ve hosted offsites in Turkey, Portugal, Mexico, Thailand, Colombia, Italy, Ireland, and more, with still more to come!&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2&gt;About the role&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Circle sales team is small but mighty. We&#39;re looking for a seasoned leader to join our team and lead a group of 7-8 Account Executives. The Sales Manager is a key leadership position at Circle responsible for hiring, and coaching a team of Account Executives to hit aggressive revenue targets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is a rare opportunity. Circle is an incredibly fast-growing PLG company with an expanding international market, an expanding suite of products and a world-class culture. The person that takes on this role, will be integral to Circle&#39;s success.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What you&#39;ll be doing&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’re building trust.&lt;/strong&gt; You will be forming deep and trusting relationships with your team, to help them hit their goals in the short term and grow as sellers in the long. You’ll be holding weekly 1:1’s with each member of your team to build trust and help them achieve their work and life goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’re coaching.&lt;/strong&gt; You love to listen to calls, provide constructive feedback and see each member improve by 0.001% each day. You’ve got some experience with systems like Gong.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’re selling.&lt;/strong&gt; You love getting involved in deals and your team loves to bring you in (because they know it will help them close the deal). You know when to take control of the deal to bring it across the line, or how to step back allow the rep to get better. At the end of the day, you love hit your number, and know that sometimes you need to roll up your sleeves to get there.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’re organized and like to document things.&lt;/strong&gt; You thrive when things get messy. You’re documenting process, organizing information to make it easier for everyone to do their job. Building evergreen content in Notion on sales playbooks, rules of engagement, or libraries of calls for reps to reference for learning opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’re deep in the data.&lt;/strong&gt; You like running reports in the CRM (Hubspot), building dashboards and proposing new processes to create important data. You have strong excel and google sheets skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’re a passionately communicating.&lt;/strong&gt; You know how to create engaging, well designed presentations for sales teams. You know how to speak to the executive team, with a clear understanding of how your business runs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’re collaborating with other teams.&lt;/strong&gt; You’re building strong internal partnerships with cross-functional teams inside and beyond the Sales organization, including Sales, Product, Marketing, Revenue Operations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’re being resourceful and creative.&lt;/strong&gt; You may not have all the answers, but you will find them and come up with creative ways to solve problems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’re showing your team the way.&lt;/strong&gt; We have ambitious goals at Circle, which requires a strong work ethic. You lead by example and value hard work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What you&#39;ll need to be successful&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong alignment with our values, &lt;a href=&quot;https://circle.so/careers&quot;&gt;find our values on our career page&lt;/a&gt; if you haven’t read up on them yet. These should resonate with you. The leaders at Circle live and breath these everyday, since they know it’s the backbone to our culture.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are proficient in English (spoken, written, and reading) at a &lt;a href=&quot;https://magoosh.com/english-speaking/english-proficiency-levels-a-guide-to-determining-your-level/&quot;&gt;CEFR Level C2&lt;/a&gt; / &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.govtilr.org/&quot;&gt;ILR Level 5&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You have sales leadership experience.&lt;/strong&gt; You have 2+ years of sales management experience in a high-growth SaaS organization with a transactional sales model.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’ve been a top performer as an individual contributor.&lt;/strong&gt; You have 6+ years of sales experience as an individual contributor. Ideally, in both transactional and consultative sales role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You know how PLG works.&lt;/strong&gt; You have worked at a product-led growth company, and have a strong opinion on what developing a world-class sales motion inside a product-led organization looks like.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You’re resourceful. You may not have all the answers, but you know how to find them.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;$190,000 USD per year OTE ($125,000 USD base with an OTE of $190,000 USD)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;The cash compensation range shown is a starting point. In addition to equity, benefits and perks, your cash compensation is subject to an annual review and increase on a once per year basis.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;h2&gt;The fun stuff&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fully remote:&amp;nbsp;work from anywhere in the world!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Autonomy and trust to do your job:&amp;nbsp;we care about outcomes over everything else.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Paid time away:&amp;nbsp;all employees are given 35 days of PTO annually. We also offer a paid sabbatical after 5 years.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generous U.S. benchmarked compensation&amp;nbsp;and startup equity no matter where you are in the world.*&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Awesome medical coverage&amp;nbsp;with 100% coverage for you and your family, or medical reimbursement options where applicable!*&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Parental leave&amp;nbsp;for parents expanding their family, or just starting one.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Home office stipend&amp;nbsp;to help you get up and running.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Learning &amp;amp; development stipend&amp;nbsp;to help you level up your professional skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Annual bonus potential&amp;nbsp;for roles that don&#39;t already receive variable income or commission.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Company retreats:&amp;nbsp;Twice a year, the Circle team gets together for a fully paid company retreat in incredible places around the world! We’ve had past retreats in Colombia, Portugal, and Mexico, with more planned on the horizon.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Check out our&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://careers.circle.so/&quot;&gt;Careers&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;page for more.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;*&lt;em&gt;Your role, location and unique circumstance may affect this.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Diversity, Equity &amp;amp; Inclusion&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a fully-remote international company, diversity is baked into our DNA. Here’s how our CEO, Sid Yadav, frames our hiring mission: “let’s find talent in underserved and under-represented corners of the world, set them up to do the best work of their lives, and in turn, change their life.” To achieve this hiring mission, we offer competitive&amp;nbsp;U.S. benchmarked&amp;nbsp;compensation no matter where someone’s located in the world, and we proactively seek candidates who expand representation of backgrounds, cultures and lived experiences in our teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Equal Employment Opportunity&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Circle is an equal opportunity employer and as such, we do not discriminate on the basis of race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, age, disability, or any other characteristic protected by applicable laws.&amp;nbsp;If you require any accommodations during the recruitment process, please let us know and we will work with you to meet your needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;&quot;&gt;
&lt;h3 class=&quot;&quot;&gt;How We Use Candidate Data&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Circle, we are committed to protecting your personal information. As a job applicant, the personal data you provide to us is collected and processed in accordance with the&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR)&lt;/strong&gt; in the EU and the &lt;strong&gt;California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA)&lt;/strong&gt;. This notice outlines the types of personal information we collect, the purpose for collecting it, and your rights.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Information We Collect:&lt;/strong&gt; We collect the following categories of personal information from job applicants:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contact information (such as name, email address, phone number)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Employment history and qualifications&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Education history&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;References and any other information you choose to share with us during the application process&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Purpose of Collection:&lt;/strong&gt; We collect this information for the following purposes:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To assess your qualifications and suitability for the position&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To communicate with you during the recruitment process&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;To comply with legal and regulatory obligations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Rights Under GDPR and CCPA:&lt;/strong&gt; You have the following rights regarding your personal information:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The right to request access to the personal information we hold about you.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The right to request the deletion of your personal information, subject to certain legal exceptions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The right to opt out of the sale of your personal information (Note: We do not sell personal information).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information about how we handle your personal data or to exercise your rights, please refer to our full &lt;a href=&quot;https://circle.so/privacy&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Privacy Policy&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;By submitting your application, you acknowledge that you have read and understood this privacy notice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;[In order to requisition 740]&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Join Our Engineering team!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a &lt;strong&gt;Solutions Architect with expertise in Salesforce &lt;/strong&gt;to join our team to partner with different cross-functional teams across the company and provide technical and product leadership for the engineering team. This role will balance high-level solution architecture responsibilities with hands-on development, guiding the team in technical best practices while working closely with stakeholders, product managers, developers, and UX designers, to deliver exceptional customer-centric solutions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About You:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience Level: &lt;/strong&gt;Architect/Principal&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Solution Design &amp;amp; Architecture:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the architecture and design of complex web- and Salesforce-based solutions, ensuring they align with business goals and best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define data models, application components, and integration strategies for seamless functionality across multiple systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create and document technical architectures that leverage Salesforce features and capabilities (e.g., Sales Cloud, Service Cloud, Marketing Cloud).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure the scalability, security, and performance of all solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Stakeholder Collaboration:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with business stakeholders to understand functional and technical requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate business needs into technical solutions while ensuring alignment with Salesforce platform capabilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Customization &amp;amp; Development:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee the customization and configuration of web or Salesforce components (Apex, Visualforce, Lightning Components, etc.) to meet business objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide guidance and oversight to development teams, ensuring best practices in development and coding standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the integration of Salesforce with external systems, leveraging APIs and middleware as necessary.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Governance &amp;amp; Best Practices:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and implement best practices for solution governance, including version control, deployment, and security protocols.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct code reviews and ensure all technical deliverables align with the overall architectural vision.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure compliance with Salesforce’s security guidelines and data protection standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Leadership:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a subject matter expert on Salesforce, staying updated on platform innovations and new releases.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Play an active role in the development and customization of Salesforce components using Apex, Visualforce, Lightning Components, and other platform tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive continuous improvement by identifying new tools, techniques, and approaches to enhance software solutions and practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to complex integrations and customizations, working side-by-side with the development team to solve technical challenges.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Modern Web Application Development:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience designing and building web applications using modern front-end/back-end technologies (e.g., React, Angular, Node.js, or similar).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leverage modern development practices like microservices, RESTful APIs, and responsive web design when building solutions that integrate with Salesforce and other platforms..&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Testing &amp;amp; Quality Assurance:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define testing strategies and lead quality assurance activities to validate that solutions meet business and technical requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee the resolution of any technical issues or bugs in a timely manner.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8+ years of experience in solution architecture, with 3+ years of experience in Salesforce platform architecture and development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of designing and implementing scalable, high-performing solutions both with standard web technologies as well as on the Salesforce platform.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep experience with Salesforce products (e.g., Sales Cloud, Service Cloud, Marketing Cloud) and third-party integrations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Skills:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of modern web technologies such as JavaScript frameworks (e.g., React, Angular) and back-end services (e.g., Node.js, Python).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient in Salesforce development tools such as Apex, Visualforce, Lightning Components, and Salesforce DX.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expertise in Salesforce integration patterns, APIs, web services, and middleware solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Salesforce Architect certifications (e.g., Application Architect, System Architect) are highly desirable.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent communication and interpersonal skills to collaborate effectively with both technical and non-technical stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You’ll Love:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leading, mentoring, and coaching both clients and Modus teammates from the comfort of home.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep diving into customer needs and translating them into actionable requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exploring new tech and continuously learning—because software is always evolving!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sharing your knowledge and participating actively in the community.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Team Collaboration:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Overlap with some EST hours daily is expected.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Reliable high-speed internet is a must!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Team Culture:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At Modus, a fast-growing, remote-first company, you’ll experience various exciting projects! Here’s a taste of what you might do:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Giving back&lt;/strong&gt;: Be an active participant through opportunities such as blog posts, open source contributions, and event speaking.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Travel &amp;amp; connections&lt;/strong&gt;: Meet fantastic people during our remote meet-ups! It’s all about collaboration and fun! Global environment and diversity at its best.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Teaching and learning&lt;/strong&gt;: Work in active teams on internal and external projects, staying up-to-date with the latest technologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Being a self starter:&amp;nbsp; &lt;/strong&gt;Autonomy and proactivity are the key to succeed at Modus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Client interaction: &lt;/strong&gt;Represent Modus and our values while connecting directly with our clients, some of the world’s biggest brands.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Growth&lt;/strong&gt;: Enjoy comprehensive learning benefits, with access to over 12,000 courses. Your growth is our priority!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About us&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Founded in 2011, Modus is a global, fully remote team of world-class technologists who thrive in a collaborative, innovative environment. We were fully remote before it was cool! We support organizations on their digital transformation journey through strategic consulting and full lifecycle product development, partnering with industry leaders including Atlassian, GitHub and AWS. Recognized as one of the Inc. 5000 Fastest Growing Private Companies for nine years and a top remote work company by FlexJobs, we have helped some of the world’s largest brands deliver powerful digital experiences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We combine boutique expertise with enterprise-scale capabilities. If you&#39;re a skilled Solutions Architect professional passionate about solving complex challenges for Fortune 500 companies and beyond, we want to hear from you.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Perks of working with us:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Remote work with flexible working hours&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Modus Global Office Program: for when you want to get out of your home, we offer on-demand access to private offices, meeting rooms, co-working spaces and business lounges in locations in over 120 countries.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Employee Referral Program.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Client Referral Program.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Travel according to client or team needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The chance to work side-by-side with thought leaders in emerging tech.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Access to more than 12,000 courses with a licensed Coursera account.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Possibility to obtain paid certification/courses if they align with company goals and are relevant to the employee&#39;s role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Additional benefits might apply contingent on&amp;nbsp;your location.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;By joining our team, you’ll be part of a winning squad that plays to each other’s strengths and celebrates every success together. Apply now and show us you’ve got what it takes to take your consulting skills to the next level with Modus Create!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;[In order to requisition&amp;nbsp; 1942]&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Join Our Product Team!&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an &lt;strong&gt;Aha! Expert - Product Manager&lt;/strong&gt; to join our team to partner with different cross-functional teams across the company and provide to our clients the best solutions.&lt;/p&gt;
